title: Launch Roundup: SpaceX to launch two Starlink missions; China to launch Chang Zheng 5
summary: A brand new week of spaceflight is approaching with SpaceX preparing to launch two Starlink missions, China getting ready to send two payloads to orbit, including one on the powerful Chang Zheng 5 (CZ-5) rocket, and Roscosmos preparing to launch Russian-built satellites to orbit atop Soyuz.

title: A little US company makes history by landing on the Moon
Intuitive Machines lands on the moon
summary: A robotic lander developed by Intuitive Machines landed safely on the moon Feb. 22, becoming the first privately developed spacecraft to touch down on the moon and the first American spacecraft to do so in more than half a century.

title: Avanti to integrate Telesat Lightspeed LEO broadband services
summary: British satellite broadband operator Avanti Communications announced plans Feb. 22 to integrate the low Earth orbit services Canada’s Telesat aims to bring online in 2027 with its regional geostationary network.

title: NGA goes big on commercial satellite data with $290 million ‘Luno’ program
summary: The National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency seeks to leverage commercial satellite imagery and data analytics to enhance its global monitoring capabilities
